calyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/statuscategory/3","id":3,"key":"done","colorName":"green","name":"Done"}},"components":[],"timeoriginalestimate":null,"customfield_13000":null,"description":"Hi all,\n\n  \nIn the user guide for 3.0 available here\n\n  \nhttp://www.eucalyptus.com/sites/all/files/docs/3.0/ug.pdf\n\n  \nAt page 14\n\n  \nPoint number 11:\n\n  \n\ndd if=<image_name> of=rootfs.img bs=1 skip=32256 count=1024000\n\n  \nThe above command can take lot of time to complete execution. We have seen\ntrial users on IRC reporting system is processing the command for many hours.\n\n  \nA short tip around this part could be to increase the block size, for example\none could have the block size as 512 and then divide the skip and count values\nby the same 512 number use the new values, the dd finishes up fast.\n\n  \n\ndd if=<image_name> of=rootfs.img bs=512 skip=63 count=2000\n\nThis tip could be as well found on the old community wiki available here:\n\n  \nhttp://open.eucalyptus.com/wiki/creating-images-iso-kvm--\n\n  \nCheck the \"extract filesystem section\" under that a <B>NOTE</B> is there.\n\n  \nPlease let me know your thoughts and if it makes sense to add this tip to the\nuser guide.\n\nThanks,\n\nDeependra\n\n","customfield_13200":null,"customfield_11300":null,"customfield_11500":null,"timetracking":{},"customfield_10401":null,"customfield_10005":null,"customfield_10600":null,"customfield_12900":null,"attachment":[],"aggregatetimeestimate":null,"summary":"adding a short tip in user guide at page 14","creator":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=agrimm","name":"agrimm","key":"agrimm","accountId":"557058:9ebc3512-73d8-45c9-85de-4325aaa62488","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/0e947b5413f5d57fba29a8ea5412f773?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FownerId%3Dagrimm%26avatarId%3D10500%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/0e947b5413f5d57fba29a8ea5412f773